Name: P10-19
checklistText:
Boost Programs

    11 - Earth orbit insertion monitor
        Sequence of Events:
            V75 Enter is not keyed unless the liftoff discrete fails and P11 does not start automatically.
            
            P11 displayed - Average G on.
            V06 N62
                Inertial Velocity Magnitude XXXXX. ft/s
                Altitude Rate XXXXX. ft/s
                Altitude XXXX.X nmi
            Pitch/roll polynomial start at liftoff +11.85 seconds.
            Terminate polynomial at liftoff +161.35 seconds.
            V82E Orbital parameter display.
            Flashing V16 N44 
                Apogee Altitude XXXX.X nmi
                Perigee Altitude XXXX.X nmi
                TFF XXbXX min/s
            PRO
            V37E 00E - Average G off.
            
            V46E While in P11 will terminate polynomial computations and enable the RHC to steer the Saturn vehicle through the AGC interface

    15 - TLI Init/Cutoff
        Sequence of Events:
            V37E 15E
            V06 N33:
                GET of TB6 (TLI TIG)
                R1: 00XXX   hours
                R2: 000XX   minutes
                R3: 0XX.xx  seconds

            Load TIG if computer is incorrect
            PRO

            V06 N14:
                R1: VC/O XXXXX ft/s

            Load dV if incorrect
            PRO

            V06 N95
                R1: TFI XXbxx min/sec   (Countdown to Ignition)
                R2: VG  XXXXX ft/s      (Remaining ft/s dV in burn)
                R3: VI  XXXXX ft/s      (Current craft dV)
